Cape Town Filled with excitement mixed with a bit of nerves, Kai April took his first steps on a 12-year adventure when he ambled through the gates of Bergvliet Primary School on Wednesday.Read: Superhero Kai is off to 'big school&quot; Despite struggling to sleep on Tuesday night, he was in a cheerful mood and buzzing on Wednesday morning. Sadly, he didn't run into any of his friends while making his way to his new classroom. Hopefully, he will make new friends and forge new relationships. Here's hoping he stays out of trouble too.He may find out soon enough that life may not be full of comic book superheroes but there will be other genuine heroes such as teachers and sport coaches along the way on his school journey.Weekend Argus